The service was awesome and friendly...
The seafood pho was off the hook!
Seafood humor.....mussels, shrimp,squid very fresh.
Two kinds of noodles in a med spicy broth.
Plenty of condiments to season to your liking.
This place is attached to Lee Lee Asian market.
If you have never been there, you may be surprised by the fishy smell that comes from the live aquarium they have in the butcher dept.
You get used to it after awhile....but it does bother some folk.
NOT ME!
I'll be back to PHO 68!
Recommend .

Best Vietnamese fresh rolls anywhere in Arizona!
We always have the barbecued pork fresh rolls and they are very tasty and good.
Their Pho is good too.
The only thing that bothered us was the fishy smell creeping in from the adjacent asian grocery store called Lee-Lee's.
But worth the trip...  By the way, we love just about every dish they make, especially #47, beef with vegetables and pan fried wide noodles.

Ok first off the odor is from the store not Pho 68.
IMO the owners have done a fantastic job with combating any odor with the decor (live plants, waterfalls, etc.).
We eat here once a week or more.
To the food: Coming from Seattle we went to numerous PHO restaurants in the valley only to be disappointed.
We went to PHo68 after shopping at Lee Lee's one day and ever since it is our primary stop for Vietnamese food in the valley.
Their Pho broth is thick and rich (NOT CLOUDY!).
In Seattle I'd order the onions in fatty broth to mix in.
No need here.
9/10.
Their meatballs are well made and just the right flavor.
No tooth killing elements.
The other dishes are made with the same attention to detail.
My son love their fried rice.
I consistently order the stew.
And it's a rarity to find a place that KNOWS just how to cook amazing shrimp so that you don't have to pull the tails (crunchy but not chewy.
Great work!).
Service.
Awesome!
I've never had a bad day there.
Everyone is friendly.
Banter is wonderful.
1 star people.
Sorry if your specific single experience was bad but I must say give the food and staff a 2nd chance.
Coming form someone that's been to 20+ Vietnamese restaurants you won't be disappointed twice.

